parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page parameter is used to paginate the results returned by the API. It specifies the page number of the results to be returned. By default, if the page parameter is not provided, the API returns results from page 0. The page parameter takes a non-negative integer value. If an invalid or negative value is provided, the API returns an error.

brand.description: The brand filter is used to retrieve a list of products from a specific brand. By entering a brand name, you can retrieve all products associated with that brand. If you leave the brand field empty or don't include it in your API request, the API will return a list of all available products from all brands.  The brand filter is case-sensitive, so make sure to enter the brand name exactly as it appears in our "All Brands" endpoint. If you enter an incorrect or misspelled brand name, the API will not return any results.

category.description: The category filter is used to retrieve a list of products from a specific category. By entering a category name, you can retrieve all products associated with that category. If you leave the category field empty or don't include it in your API request, the API will return a list of all available products from all categories.  The category filter is case-sensitive, so make sure to enter the category name exactly as it appears in our "All Categories" endpoint. If you enter an incorrect or misspelled category name, the API will not return any results.

from.description: This Date filter is used to retrieve all products released after a specified date. By entering a date in the format YYYY-MM-DD, you can retrieve all products that were released on or after that date. If you leave this Date field empty or don't include it in your API request, the API will return all available products. All categories except "Desktops" supports date filters

to.description: This Date filter is used to retrieve all products released before a specified date. By entering a date in the format YYYY-MM-DD, you can retrieve all products that were released on or before that date. If you leave this Date field empty or don't include it in your API request, the API will return all available products. All categories except "Desktops" supports date filters
